#. type: section{#2}
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:2 latex/en/iTestClient.tex:2
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:6
msgid ""
"iTestServer offers an easy way to organise a database of questions and "
"answers.  It makes use of colours in a way that makes this even easier.  It "
"features a simple rich text editor that allows you to format your questions "
"just the way you like."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:9
msgid ""
"iTestServer is also used as the server, to which client computers then "
"connect in order to retrieve a test.  It can save test sessions for later "
"viewing and allows you to view and print statistics."
msgstr ""

#. type: section{#2}
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:11
msgid "User interface"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:13
msgid "\\sshot{itestserver-1_2_0-main-top}{The menu bar and the tool bar}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:15
msgid ""
"The menu bar provides access to different actions, like opening, saving and "
"closing a database in the File menu, actions related to the current view and "
"language in the View menu, database statistics and other database-related "
"actions in the Database menu or a link to this documentation and an update "
"checker in the Help menu."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:20
msgid ""
"The tool bar features icons for actions that can also be found in the "
"menus.  The most notable ones are the five checkable icons which follow the "
"Save button.  You can use these to switch view to editing questions "
"(Questions), writing notes (Comments), creating flags (Flags), configuring "
"and running the server (Server mode) and viewing saved sessions (Saved "
"sessions).  Of course, this only works when a database is open."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:22
msgid ""
"\\sshot{itestserver-1_2_0-questions-top}{The menu bar and the tool bar when "
"a database is open}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:24
msgid ""
"The middle part of the window features a list of recently used databases."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:26
msgid "\\sshot{itest-1_0_2-main-list}{Recently used databases}"
msgstr ""

#. type: section{#2}
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:28
msgid "Creating a database"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:33
msgid ""
"To create a new database, click the New button in the File menu, in the tool "
"bar or under the list of recent databases.  Type in a name for the "
"database.  Please choose wisely, this name shouldn't be too long and should "
"represent the content of the database well.  After this, choose a name for "
"the database file."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:35
msgid ""
"You can always change the database name later (although it's not "
"recommended)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:37
msgid "\\sshot{itestserver-1_4_0-questions-dbi-name}{Database name}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:39
msgid ""
"The database also contains a date, which you can set to be the date of the "
"last save, or to stay the same permanently (this is useful, if you want to "
"keep the date when you created the database)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:41
msgid "\\sshot{itest-1_0_2-questions-dbi-date}{Database date}"
msgstr ""

#. type: subsection{#2}
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:43
msgid "Editing questions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:47
msgid ""
"To create a new question, you can either go to the Question menu and click "
"Add, or click Add in the tool bar or below the list of questions.  Type in a "
"name for the question -- this name should not give a hint about the answer "
"of the question.  It should be a unique, descriptive name for the question "
"which will remind you about the topic of the question."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:49
msgid "The new question will appear in the list of questions."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:51
msgid "\\sshot{itest-1_0_2-questions-filtered2-list-top}{List of questions}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:56
msgid ""
"This list can be filtered, which is useful when you have a lot of questions, "
"maybe even hundreds of them.  There are 5 radio buttons at the top.  The "
"first of them that says All shows all questions (unless the Search field is "
"yellow or red), the second one with the green icon shows easy questions "
"only, the third button (the orange one) questions with medium difficulty "
"only, the fourth (the red one) difficult questions only and finally the "
"fifth with the flag icon shows questions with a selected flag only (you can "
"select the flag in the combo box below it).  If you type a keyword into the "
"Search field, it turns yellow if any question matches your search or red if "
"none found."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:58
msgid ""
"\\sshot{itest-1_0_2-questions-filtered2-list-bottom}{Buttons below the list "
"of questions}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:61
msgid ""
"Below the list, there are several buttons. They are shortcuts for actions "
"located in the Question menu.  They mean Add, Duplicate, Delete, Move up and "
"Move down, respectively."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:64
msgid ""
"When you select a question to edit, it will appear on the right side of this "
"list, in a section called Selected question.  Here you can type in the text "
"of the question, its answers and select the correct one(s)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:66
msgid "\\sshot{itestserver-1_4_0-questions-edit}{Question editor}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:68
msgid ""
"The topmost part of this section allows you to change its name, flag and "
"difficulty."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:70
msgid ""
"\\sshot{itestserver-1_2_0-questions-edit-basic}{Question name, flag, group "
"and difficulty}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:77
msgid ""
"Below this, you can see the basic formatting tools.  The first two buttons "
"allow you to revert the last action (left arrow) or redo a reverted action "
"(right arrow).  There's one combo box for choosing a font and one for the "
"font size.  Then there are buttons for switching to bold (B), italic (I) and "
"underlined (U) text.  Next to these, there is a button for choosing the "
"colour of the text.  And finally, L stands for align left, C for centre, R "
"for right and J for justify."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:79
msgid "\\sshot{itest-1_0_2-questions-edit-formatting}{Text formatting options}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:86
msgid ""
"Attachments allow you to add graphics (Scalable Vector Graphics) to "
"questions.  You can use programs such as Inkscape to create an SVG and then "
"import it into iTest by clicking the plus button.  To remove an attachment, "
"select it and click the minus button.  If you need to change an SVG item "
"(either its name or the actual image), click the edit button located next to "
"the minus button.  The last button in the row allows you to export an SVG "
"from iTest, which is useful if you've deleted the original SVG file and want "
"to make changes to it.  SVG support was introduced in iTest 1.3."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:88
msgid "\\sshot{itestserver-1_3_0-questions-edit-svg_tools}{SVG tools}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:90
msgid ""
"Do not forget to click Apply or Save after any change you make to a "
"question, because otherwise it will not be saved."
msgstr ""

#. type: subsection{#2}
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:92
msgid "Printing questions and tests"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:96
msgid ""
"When you've created a database with several questions, you may want to print "
"them.  In order to do so, go to the Database menu and select Print "
"questions.  A window will show up."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:98
msgid ""
"\\sshot{itestserver-1_3_0-print_questions}{Print questions dialogue window}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:102
msgid ""
"If you want all questions to be printed, simply click Add all.  If you want "
"to print questions with a specific flag or flags, select Flags (this is the "
"default) and double click the desired flags.  If you want to select "
"questions to print manually, select Questions and double click any question "
"you want to print."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:109
msgid ""
"If you want to specify advanced options, check the checkbox labelled "
"Advanced.  If Print statistics is checked, statistics will be printed for "
"each question which has already been used in a test.  If you want to disable "
"formatting, uncheck Print formatted questions.  If you want to use the print-"
"outs for testing purposes, be sure to check Print a test.  This way, correct "
"answers will not be highlighted.  Lastly, if you want to print SVG "
"attachments, check Print graphics."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:111
msgid "Support for printing was introduced in iTest 1.3."
msgstr ""

#. type: subsection{#2}
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:113
msgid "Comments"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:117
msgid ""
"Use comments to write down anything you want.  This could be reminders, "
"notes, to-dos and so on.  Comments are saved within the database file and "
"are therefore unique for each database."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:119
msgid "You can even use the formatting tools to make your notes look better."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:121
msgid "\\sshot{itestserver-1_2_0-comments-formatting}{Comments editor}"
msgstr ""

#. type: subsection{#2}
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:123
msgid "Using flags"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:127
msgid ""
"Imagine you have a database of questions from biology.  These need to be "
"divided into several categories, for example fauna and flora.  You can do "
"this with flags."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:129
msgid "To create a new flag, click a checkbox next to an empty field."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:131
msgid "\\sshot{itest-1_0_2-flags-checkbox}{An empty flag}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:135
msgid ""
"Next, type in a name. \\quo{Biology - fauna} is a good example.  If this is "
"the first flag you created, all questions will automatically be assigned "
"this flag.  If there are any questions assigned, you can no longer disable "
"the flag (because it is \\quo{in use})."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:137
msgid ""
"\\sshot{itestserver-1_2_0-flags-disabledcheckbox}{A flag which has been "
"assigned to one question}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:140
msgid ""
"Each flag has a different colour and any question with that flag has the "
"same colour as well.  Flags are also useful when you want to set up a test "
"with only those questions that are assigned a certain flag."
msgstr ""

#. type: section{#2}
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:142
msgid "Setting up a server"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:146
msgid ""
"To hold a test session, you will need to set up the server.  It is "
"recommended to have a printer connected to this server.  Click the Server "
"mode button in the tool bar."
msgstr ""

#. type: enumerate
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:149
msgid "Now you have several options. {\\bf You can:}"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:154
msgid ""
"{\\bf set up a session using all the questions in the database.}\\\\ Leave "
"the Advanced checkbox unchecked. \\inlineimg{itest-1_0_2-server_settings-"
"advanced_unchecked} Proceed to step 2."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:165
msgid ""
"{\\bf set up a session using only those questions, which have a certain flag "
"or flags.}\\\\ Check the Advanced checkbox. \\inlineimg{itest-1_0_2-"
"server_settings-advanced_checked} Select flags. \\inlineimg{itest-1_0_2-"
"server_settings-advanced-flags_radiobutton}\\\\ Move those flags, which you "
"want to use in the test, into the Used list by selecting them and clicking "
"the right arrow.  \\inlineimg{itest-1_0_2-server_settings-advanced-"
"rightarrow}\\\\ If you want, you can also set a separate pass mark (i.e. "
"minimum number of correct answers to pass the test) for each flag.  iTest "
"will make sure each student is asked a sufficient amount of questions with a "
"flag for which a pass mark is specified (a value higher than 0), so that "
"each student has a chance to pass.  To pass the test, each condition must be "
"fulfilled, that means all the pass marks specified here and the global pass "
"mark (see step 2).  This feature was introduced in iTest 1.2.\\\\\\\\ \\img"
"{itestserver-1_2_0-server_settings-advanced-flags-passmarks}{scale="
"\\sshotscale}"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:172
msgid ""
"{\\bf set up a session using only manually selected questions.}\\\\ Check "
"the Advanced checkbox. \\inlineimg{itest-1_0_2-server_settings-"
"advanced_checked} Select questions. \\inlineimg{itest-1_0_2-server_settings-"
"advanced-questions_radiobutton}\\\\ Move those questions, which you want to "
"use in the test, into the Used list by selecting them and clicking the right "
"arrow.  \\inlineimg{itest-1_0_2-server_settings-advanced-rightarrow}"
msgstr ""

#. type: enumerate
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:174
msgid "Below, there are several parameters to set."
msgstr ""

#. type: item[#1]
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:181
msgid "Test name:"
msgstr ""

#. type: description
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:181
msgid ""
"Unless you want to specify a custom test name, you may leave the checkbox "
"unchecked.  The database name will be used as the test name.  However, if "
"you do want to specify a custom test name, check the checkbox and type in a "
"name into the field next to it.\\\\\\\\ \\img{itest-1_0_2-server_settings-"
"test_name}{scale=\\sshotscale}"
msgstr ""

#. type: item[#1]
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:187
msgid "Number of questions:"
msgstr ""

#. type: description
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:187
msgid ""
"Here you can choose the number of questions each student will be asked.  The "
"questions will be chosen automatically (limited only by your settings from "
"step 1), different for each student (if not possible, at least in a "
"different order).  You may also choose to use all available questions by "
"selecting \\quo{maximum}.\\\\\\\\ \\img{itest-1_0_2-server_settings-"
"num_of_questions}{scale=\\sshotscale}"
msgstr ""

#. type: item[#1]
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:194
msgid "Groups:"
msgstr ""

#. type: description
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:194
msgid ""
"Check this checkbox to allow a single question per group to appear in one "
"test only.  This means that once a question from a group is randomly chosen, "
"no other questions from the same group may be chosen.  If you have some "
"groups with more questions, checking this checkbox will cause the maximum "
"number of questions to decrease, because each group then acts as a single "
"question.  This feature was introduced in iTest 1.2.\\\\\\\\ \\img"
"{itestserver-1_2_0-server_settings-groups}{scale=\\sshotscale}"
msgstr ""

#. type: item[#1]
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:198
msgid "Pass mark:"
msgstr ""

#. type: description
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:198
msgid ""
"Here you can choose the minimum number of correct answers the student must "
"have in order to pass the exam.\\\\\\\\ \\img{itest-1_0_2-server_settings-"
"pass_mark}{scale=\\sshotscale}"
msgstr ""

#. type: item[#1]
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:206
msgid "Time:"
msgstr ""

#. type: description
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:206
msgid ""
"You may choose to specify a certain exam time by selecting \\quo{(Time for) "
"the whole test} and specifying the time.  However, you can also specify the "
"time per question, which will then be multiplied by the number of questions "
"in the test in order to obtain the total exam time.  This is useful, when "
"you want to say, that students should have, say, one minute for each "
"question.  This will not prevent the students from using 1 minute 30 seconds "
"of their time for one question and 30 seconds for another.\\\\\\\\ \\img"
"{itest-1_0_2-server_settings-time}{scale=\\sshotscale}"
msgstr ""

#. type: enumerate
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:209
msgid ""
"You are now ready to start the server.  Click the Start server button or go "
"to the Server menu and select Start server."
msgstr ""

#. type: enumerate
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:215
msgid ""
"If you haven't configured the printer yet, you will be asked to do so.  When "
"you select the printer to use and configure it, you will have to click "
"Print.  Don't worry, nothing will be printed yet.  This setting will be used "
"when the students finish their tests, in order to print the results.  "
"Everything is done automatically, you will be informed about any activity of "
"the printer via the server log."
msgstr ""

#. type: enumerate
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:219
msgid ""
"If you don't want to print the results and you want to keep them in an "
"electronic form instead (so that you can mail them to the students, for "
"instance), you can use software like PDF Creator (free), Adobe Acrobat or "
"Macromedia FlashPaper (probably the most suitable) and configure iTest to "
"use the virtual printer they provide.  Please note that this is only needed "
"under Windows.  Computers running Mac OS X and most Linux distributions can "
"create PDF files out-of-the-box."
msgstr ""

#. type: enumerate
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:223
msgid ""
"Now you may connect client computers.  See the iTestClient documentation for "
"details on how to do this."
msgstr ""

#. type: subsection{#2}
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:225
msgid "Off-line usage"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:227
msgid ""
"In case there is no network available, you will need to load the test into "
"each client computer manually:"
msgstr ""

#. type: enumerate
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:230
msgid "Set up a server the normal way."
msgstr ""

#. type: enumerate
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:234
msgid ""
"Export a test by going to the Server menu and selecting Export test.  Save "
"it to a flash disk or any other kind of removable media.  Do not stop the "
"server now!"
msgstr ""

#. type: enumerate
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:236
msgid "Plug the media into a client computer."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:240
msgid ""
"Under {\\bf Windows}, you can open the Explorer window, go to the folder "
"with your exported test and double click the file.  Once it is loaded into "
"iTestClient, you may unplug the media (it is no longer needed) and do the "
"same with the rest of the client computers."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:245
msgid ""
"Under {\\bf any} other {\\bf operating system} (and Windows, if you prefer "
"this way), run iTestClient, manually locate the file on the media and load "
"it.  Once it is loaded into iTestClient, you may unplug the media (it is no "
"longer needed) and do the same with the rest of the client computers.  For "
"further details on how to do this, see the iTestClient documentation."
msgstr ""

#. type: enumerate
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:249
msgid ""
"When the students finish their tests, plug the removable media into each "
"client computer and copy the file, which was generated by iTestClient.  By "
"default, it is located in the home directory (under Windows, this is "
"something like {\\tt C:\\textbackslash{}Documents and Settings\\textbackslash"
"{}User}).  Preferably, copy all the files from all the client computers into "
"a separate directory on your removable media."
msgstr ""

#. type: enumerate
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:256
msgid ""
"Plug the removable media into the server.  From the Server menu, select Add "
"off-line clients.  Select the directory on the removable media with all the "
"clients' files.  iTest should load all of them automatically, and their "
"results should be printed.  You may now stop the server."
msgstr ""

#. type: section{#2}
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:258
msgid "Viewing saved sessions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:261
msgid ""
"In order to be able to view past sessions, you need to check the Save "
"session option the Server menu when the server is running.  It will then be "
"saved when you stop the server."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:266
msgid ""
"To view a session, switch the view to Saved sessions by clicking the icon in "
"the toolbar.  You will see the session in the list of sessions.  Double "
"click its item in this list.  The session will be loaded and ready for "
"viewing."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:268
msgid "\\sshot{itest-1_0_2-saved_sessions-list}{List of saved sessions}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:270
msgid ""
"You can now view the results of a student by clicking a name in the list of "
"students."
msgstr ""

#. type: subsection{#2}
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:272
msgid "Printing"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:276
msgid ""
"When you're viewing a saved session, you can also print results of a "
"student, of all students or a summary of the session.  In orded to do this, "
"go to the Session menu and click one of the first three options, according "
"to what you want to print.  You can only print results of a student if a "
"student is selected in the list of students."
msgstr ""

#. type: subsection{#2}
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:278
msgid "Exporting a log"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:283
msgid ""
"If a session has a log, you can export it as an html document.  In order to "
"do this, a session must be loaded.  To export a log, go to the Session menu "
"and select the Export log option.  Now, choose a name for the file and save "
"it."
msgstr ""

#. type: subsection{#2}
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:285
msgid "Deleting a log"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:290
msgid ""
"When a session log is no longer needed, you can delete it to save disk "
"space.  In order to do this, a session must be loaded.  To delete a log, go "
"to the Session menu and select the Delete log option.  You will be asked to "
"confirm this action."
msgstr ""

#. type: subsection{#2}
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:292
msgid "Archiving, restoring and copying a session"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:298
msgid ""
"In iTest 1.1, a new feature called archive was introduced.  The archive can "
"store sessions, which are associated with the database by its name.  When "
"you open a database, iTest checks if there are any archived sessions under "
"its name.  If so, they are all loaded and you can view them.  If you open "
"the same database on a different computer, these sessions will not be shown, "
"because they are only available on the computer where you archive them."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:301
msgid ""
"Archiving a session is easy, you just need to load the session you wish to "
"archive, go to the Session menu and select Archive session.  You'll see the "
"session jump from the list of sessions to the archive."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:303
msgid "\\sshot{itest-1_1_1-saved_sessions-archive}{List of archived sessions}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:306
msgid ""
"Restoring a session brings it back into the database.  To do so, choose "
"Restore session from the Session menu."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:308
msgid ""
"To copy a session to or from the archive, use the appropriate actions in the "
"Session menu."
msgstr ""

#. type: section{#2}
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:310
msgid "Using the statistics"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:315
msgid ""
"iTest remembers every answer of every student, correct or wrong.  The number "
"of correct and incorrect answers is saved in the database along with the "
"question.  These numbers are used to determine the difficulty of a "
"question.  If available, this information is displayed at the bottom of the "
"editor when you select a question."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:317
msgid ""
"\\sshot{itest-1_0_2-questions-statistics}{Statistics available for a "
"question}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:322
msgid ""
"By clicking \\quo{adjust difficulty}, the difficulty of the question is set "
"to the calculated one.  You can also adjust the difficulty of all questions "
"in your database.  In order to do so, select Overall statistics from the "
"Database menu.  A window will appear."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:324
msgid ""
"\\sshot{itestserver-1_2_0-statistics-window}{Overall statistics for a "
"database}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestServer.tex:326
msgid ""
"Click Adjust all to change the difficulties of all questions to the "
"calculated ones.  You can also change the difficulty of some questions only "
"by clicking the corresponding Adjust difficulty button on the right."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestClient.tex:8
msgid ""
"iTestClient is used as a client program.  It loads the test created by the "
"server and randomly chooses the questions to form a unique test for the "
"student.  It can either connect to the server over a network or load the "
"test from a file exported by the server.  When the test is over, the results "
"are saved into a file and if the client is connected over network, they are "
"automatically sent to the server.  In case of connection breakdown, the "
"backup file can be used -- it can be loaded back into the server."
msgstr ""

#. type: section{#2}
#: latex/en/iTestClient.tex:10
msgid "On-line usage"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestClient.tex:15
msgid ""
"First you will need to get a server running.  See the iTestServer "
"documentation for further details.  You should also know either the IP "
"address of the server or its network name.  For each operating system, there "
"is different way to obtain this information, and it is thus beyond the scope "
"of this documentation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestClient.tex:20
msgid ""
"When the server is running, run iTestClient on a client computer connected "
"to one network with the server.  Type the IP address of the server or its "
"name into the Server name field and by pressing Return (Enter) move to the "
"next field.  Type the server port in here and press Return (Enter) again.  "
"The client should now connect."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestClient.tex:22
msgid "\\sshot{itestwri-1_0_2-main-network}{Connecting to an iTest server}"
msgstr ""

#. type: section{#2}
#: latex/en/iTestClient.tex:24
msgid "Setting the output file location"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestClient.tex:27
msgid ""
"The output file contains the answers of the student.  It is used in case of "
"connection breakdown or in case there is no network available and the off-"
"line approach is used."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestClient.tex:29
msgid "\\sshot{itestwri-1_0_2-main-output}{Setting the output file location}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestClient.tex:32
msgid ""
"The default location is the home directory of the current user.  Under "
"Windows, this is the \\\\Documents and Settings\\\\UserName directory."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestClient.tex:35
msgid ""
"If you need to specify another location, uncheck the Use default checkbox "
"and click Browse.  You shouldn't choose any directory visible to the "
"student, least of all the desktop or the My Documents folder."
msgstr ""

#. type: section{#2}
#: latex/en/iTestClient.tex:37
msgid "Other settings"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestClient.tex:39
msgid ""
"\\sshot{itestwri-1_1_1-other_settings-hide_question_names}{Hide question "
"names}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestClient.tex:42
msgid ""
"If you do not want the students to see the names of the questions, check "
"\\quo{Hide question names, show numbers instead}.  This feature was "
"introduced in iTest 1.1."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestClient.tex:44
msgid ""
"\\sshot{itestclient-1_3_0-other_settings-do_not_show_correct_answers}{Do not "
"show correct answers}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestClient.tex:47
msgid ""
"If you do not want correct answers to be displayed at the end of the test, "
"check \\quo{Do not show correct answers at the end of the test}.  This "
"feature was introduced in iTest 1.3."
msgstr ""

#. type: section{#2}
#: latex/en/iTestClient.tex:49
msgid "Testing"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestClient.tex:51
msgid ""
"When you have configured the client, it is time to click the Ready button in "
"the lower right corner of the screen."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestClient.tex:55
msgid ""
"Now is the time for the students to enter the classroom.  They sit down in "
"front of a client computer and are presented with the Welcome screen.  They "
"type in their name and click Start."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestClient.tex:60
msgid ""
"They may choose to view the remaining time by clicking Show remaining time "
"in the bottom of the screen.  Each time they select an answer, the "
"corresponding question turns green in the list of questions.  The green "
"colour does not indicate a correct answer -- just an answer.  Whether "
"they're right or wrong, they will be informed at the end of the test (unless "
"you are using the off-line approach, which does not support this)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestClient.tex:64
msgid ""
"If a certain question contains SVG graphics, it will be displayed below the "
"text of the question.  Clicking the blue title of a picture shows it in a "
"separate window, allowing the student to resize it and thus take a closer "
"look at it.  This feature was introduced in iTest 1.3."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestClient.tex:68
msgid ""
"When they run out of time, the test is automatically ended.  In case they "
"are ready sooner than that, they can choose to finish the exam by clicking "
"Finish.  They will be asked to confirm this action."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestClient.tex:70
msgid "\\sshot{itestclient-1_2_0-newtest_button}{New test button}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: latex/en/iTestClient.tex:73
msgid ""
"When the test is over, you can start a new one by clicking the New test "
"button.  If you are using the off-line approach, the media with the test "
"file must still be connected.  This feature was introduced in iTest 1.2."
msgstr ""
